
[1]felspath

   FEL'SPATH, n. A mineral widely distributed and usually of a foliated
   structure. When in crystals or crystalline masses, it is very
   susceptible of mechanical division at natural joints. its hardness is a
   little inferior to that of quartz. There are several varieties, as
   common feldspar,the adularia, the siliceous, the glassy, the ice-spar,
   the opalescent, aventurine feldspar, petuntze, the granular, and the
   compact.
